---
---

<section id="about" class="relative border-t border-edge/40 py-32">
  <!-- Subtle glow -->
  <div
    class="pointer-events-none absolute left-0 top-0 h-px w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-accent/20 to-transparent"
  >
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
    <div class="grid gap-16 lg:grid-cols-12">
      <!-- Label column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <span
          class="font-display text-xs font-600 tracking-widest text-accent uppercase"
          >About the Event</span
        >
        <h2
          class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-800 leading-tight tracking-tight text-ivory sm:text-5xl"
        >
          Two ecosystems.<br />
          <span class="text-subtle">One builder network.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Content column -->
      <div class="space-y-8 lg:col-span-7 lg:col-start-6">
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-subtle">
          L8P Brazil is a small, invite-only gathering for Brazilian founders
          and engineers building in or connected to Silicon Valley. No panels,
          no keynotes — just focused technical sessions in Palo Alto followed
          by a closing mixer in San Francisco.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-subtle">
          We keep the group intimate so every conversation matters. If you're
          shipping code, raising rounds, or scaling infrastructure across
          borders, this is your room.
        </p>

        <!-- Stat cards -->
        <div class="mt-12 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-edge/60 bg-surface p-6">
            <span
              class="font-display text-3xl font-800 bg-gradient-to-br from-accent to-accent-dim bg-clip-text text-transparent"
              >BR + US</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
              Cross-border network of founders, engineers, and builders.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-edge/60 bg-surface p-6">
            <span
              class="font-display text-3xl font-800 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber to-amber/70 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
              >2 Days</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Six curated technical sessions and a closing mixer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-edge/60 bg-surface p-6">
            <span class="block font-display text-sm font-600 tracking-widest text-subtle uppercase">April</span>
            <span
              class="font-display text-5xl font-800 bg-gradient-to-r from-accent via-accent-dim to-amber bg-clip-text text-transparent"
              >9–10</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">2026 — Hosted at <a href="https://circuitlaunch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:underline">Circuit Launch</a>, Mountain View.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Format section -->
        <div class="mt-16">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xs font-600 tracking-widest text-accent uppercase">
            Format
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-edge/60 bg-surface p-6">
              <span class="font-display text-lg font-800 text-ivory">
                Technical Sessions — Palo Alto
              </span>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                Six focused sessions in a small-group setting. Builders share real
                work — architecture decisions, scaling challenges, and lessons from
                the trenches. No slides, no pitches.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-edge/60 bg-surface p-6">
              <span class="font-display text-lg font-800 text-ivory">
                Closing Mixer — San Francisco
              </span>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                An evening gathering to continue the conversations in a relaxed
                setting. Meet the extended network of Brazilian founders and
                engineers across the Bay Area.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Who Attends -->
        <div class="mt-16">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xs font-600 tracking-widest text-accent uppercase">
            Who Attends
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
            We curate for builders — people actively shipping products, writing code, and scaling companies across both ecosystems.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-subtle">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              Founders building venture-backed startups in the US or Brazil
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              Senior engineers at top-tier tech companies in Silicon Valley
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              Technical leaders scaling infrastructure across borders
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              Open-source contributors and developer advocates
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              Investors and operators with deep ties to both ecosystems
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Why L8P Exists -->
        <div class="mt-16">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xs font-600 tracking-widest text-accent uppercase">
            Why L8P Exists
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
            Brazil has one of the largest and most dynamic developer communities in the world, yet Brazilian builders in Silicon Valley remain scattered across companies and networks with few spaces designed specifically for them.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
            L8P Brazil exists to change that — creating a recurring, high-signal gathering where Brazilian technologists in the Valley can share knowledge, form partnerships, and strengthen the bridge between both ecosystems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
